1
00:00:15,992 --> 00:00:17,855
<i>[Man narrating]
During the Warring States Period,</i>

2
00:00:18,137 --> 00:00:21,587
<i>China was made up of
dozens of nations.</i>

3
00:00:22,521 --> 00:00:24,620
<i>Countless fights between states.</i>

4
00:00:24,913 --> 00:00:26,605
<i>Society was in devastation.</i>

5
00:00:28,143 --> 00:00:36,159
<i>The 7 largest states were known as
Qi, Chu, Yan, Han, Zhao, Wei and Qin.</i>

6
00:00:38,071 --> 00:00:39,846
<i>The rest was nearly wiped out</i>

7
00:00:39,998 --> 00:00:43,075
<i>a hundred years before the unification.</i>

8
00:00:45,931 --> 00:00:50,266
<i>Qin then conquered Han and Zhao
subsequently.</i>

9
00:01:00,915 --> 00:01:03,478
<i>Year 227 B.C.</i>

10
00:01:03,669 --> 00:01:06,420
<i>When Wei's troops marching towards
the state of Liang.</i>

11
00:01:07,075 --> 00:01:11,409
<i>they were ambushed by Liang
at Mt. Phoenix.</i>

12
00:01:11,785 --> 00:01:13,277
<i>Both sides suffered heavily.</i>

13
00:01:13,653 --> 00:01:18,136
<i>Death toll reached 3,000.</i>

14
00:01:23,200 --> 00:01:29,000
SDH/Translation: Arigon

15
00:01:37,401 --> 00:01:38,901
[Crow gargling]

16
00:01:45,701 --> 00:01:47,201
[Crow gargling]

17
00:01:51,602 --> 00:01:55,402
[Wolf howling]

18
00:02:02,201 --> 00:02:05,201
[Crow gargling]

19
00:02:08,101 --> 00:02:09,601
[Crow gargling]

20
00:02:22,602 --> 00:02:29,602
[Crow continues gargling]

21
00:02:34,003 --> 00:02:37,003
[Spring bouncing]

22
00:02:50,827 --> 00:02:52,094
Third bro.

23
00:02:55,304 --> 00:02:56,888
Third bro.

24
00:02:58,147 --> 00:03:00,152
You're not lucky as I am.

25
00:03:12,753 --> 00:03:14,253
[Crow gargling]

26
00:03:24,385 --> 00:03:26,318
Big soldier: General!
Man: Who are you?

27
00:03:26,460 --> 00:03:28,233
Liang's soldier.

28
00:03:39,134 --> 00:03:41,634
[Man gasping]

29
00:03:47,205 --> 00:03:48,335
[Yelling]

30
00:03:54,135 --> 00:03:55,535
[Spring bouncing]

31
00:04:03,906 --> 00:04:07,136
[Yelling]

32
00:04:22,837 --> 00:04:24,437
[Groaning in pain]

33
00:04:39,108 --> 00:04:40,108
[Both yelling]

34
00:04:44,209 --> 00:04:45,509
[Groaning]

35
00:04:55,210 --> 00:04:58,700
[Groaning in pain]

36
00:05:16,544 --> 00:05:22,723
<i>[Big Soldier singing]
One main road leads to homecoming</i>

37
00:05:23,563 --> 00:05:29,772
<i>My home is right at
the foot of Mt. Liang</i>

38
00:05:30,949 --> 00:05:37,389
<i>Soils are rich there
5 acres of farms</i>

39
00:05:37,717 --> 00:05:39,164
Pretty good.

40
00:05:39,353 --> 00:05:45,177
<i>5 acres of farm
What to grow?</i>

41
00:05:52,313 --> 00:05:53,339
[Big Soldier]
Let me tell you something.

42
00:05:53,436 --> 00:05:55,901
When I was a boy, I caught a boar.
My dad had me let go of it.

43
00:05:56,044 --> 00:05:57,730
You know why?

44
00:05:57,874 --> 00:05:59,784
There were boys
inside that belly.

45
00:05:59,974 --> 00:06:01,700
You have boys, huh?

46
00:06:05,678 --> 00:06:07,307
You know what,

47
00:06:07,908 --> 00:06:10,967
you're my captive now.
Hey, hey.

48
00:06:11,673 --> 00:06:12,973
[Groaning]

49
00:06:13,074 --> 00:06:14,846
You've lost few blood.

50
00:06:15,222 --> 00:06:17,332
Not a big deal.

51
00:06:19,057 --> 00:06:21,295
This is the drug developed
by my family.

52
00:06:21,446 --> 00:06:23,471
Don't spare this to anyone.

53
00:06:27,226 --> 00:06:28,598
You hurt, huh?

54
00:06:29,234 --> 00:06:31,284
Now it gonna hurt more.

55
00:06:31,385 --> 00:06:33,385
[Groaning in great pain]

56
00:06:33,476 --> 00:06:35,854
You're welcome, young man!

57
00:06:36,135 --> 00:06:39,647
Big Soldier: You'll live, you know.
Wei's General: X+@#?

58
00:06:40,193 --> 00:06:41,778
And don't curse.

59
00:06:47,649 --> 00:06:48,966
My dad said,

60
00:06:49,203 --> 00:06:53,224
Scratch when you're itchy,
Smile when you ain't lucky!

61
00:06:56,579 --> 00:06:58,071
Pretty good.

62
00:06:58,872 --> 00:07:00,072
Mmm?

63
00:07:00,273 --> 00:07:01,273
[Yelling]

64
00:07:11,274 --> 00:07:12,274
[Moaning]

65
00:07:16,705 --> 00:07:18,305
[Blood splashing]
Ah!

66
00:07:28,112 --> 00:07:29,605
General.

67
00:07:33,539 --> 00:07:34,566
Deputy General Yu.

68
00:07:34,708 --> 00:07:36,276
Yu:
Yes, I am.

69
00:07:36,158 --> 00:07:38,212
Wei's General:
Hang on a sec.

70
00:07:39,470 --> 00:07:41,563
Wei's General:
Why you're here?

71
00:07:42,176 --> 00:07:44,229
Yu:
In pursuit of Liang's men.

72
00:07:47,443 --> 00:07:50,395
Wei's General: In pursuit?
How many have you killed?

73
00:07:50,441 --> 00:07:51,655
Wei's General:
Speak.

74
00:07:51,829 --> 00:07:52,917
Yu: One.

75
00:07:53,106 --> 00:07:55,709
- My men must fight hard.
Yu: Liang's came hard on us...

76
00:07:55,880 --> 00:07:57,244
Wei's General:
Defend our nation with our lives.

77
00:07:57,387 --> 00:08:01,100
Yu: Please, for the sake of...
- AWOL personnel must face penalty.

78
00:08:01,264 --> 00:08:05,356
Yu: General, my company was
all gone last night.

79
00:08:05,469 --> 00:08:08,965
Wei's General:
Gone? I was there last night.

80
00:08:09,155 --> 00:08:11,253
In fact, we were ambushed.

81
00:08:11,442 --> 00:08:13,632
And you were the traitor.

82
00:08:25,047 --> 00:08:27,143
You're so cruel.

83
00:08:27,247 --> 00:08:29,828
He saved your life, and you took his.

84
00:08:31,374 --> 00:08:32,674
Hey, hey, hey,

85
00:08:32,775 --> 00:08:34,801
what you gonna do, huh?

86
00:08:35,688 --> 00:08:36,855
He was right.

87
00:08:37,053 --> 00:08:39,011
You're all dead.

88
00:08:39,295 --> 00:08:40,694
Kill me.

89
00:08:40,883 --> 00:08:42,797
I don't kill POW.

90
00:08:43,635 --> 00:08:47,401
Now, keep begging. I might let
you go, if you tried hard enough.

91
00:08:47,570 --> 00:08:49,390
Wei's General:
Just kill me.

92
00:08:50,809 --> 00:08:52,255
You really want to die?

93
00:08:52,632 --> 00:08:54,449
Here, let me help you.

94
00:08:59,900 --> 00:09:01,114
Too bad,

95
00:09:02,048 --> 00:09:04,611
I failed my mission.

96
00:09:26,780 --> 00:09:28,793
[Big Soldier chuckling]
Want to die, huh?

97
00:09:28,835 --> 00:09:30,888
Die another day.

98
00:09:45,607 --> 00:09:49,197
Prince Wen, we've accomplished.

99
00:09:49,977 --> 00:09:54,323
Like he said, to die with
dignity in a battle field.

100
00:09:54,653 --> 00:09:55,866
You're AWOL.

101
00:09:56,055 --> 00:09:57,967
Big Soldier:
Not exactly. Just playing dead.

102
00:09:58,110 --> 00:10:00,070
My dad said, no shame for
living to fight another day,

103
00:10:00,213 --> 00:10:01,472
only for being dead in vain.

104
00:10:01,662 --> 00:10:04,402
Poor Third bro didn't listen to me.
He refused to play dead.

105
00:10:04,504 --> 00:10:06,936
- How much am I worth?
- It doesn't hurt to tell you.

106
00:10:07,126 --> 00:10:09,616
General alive: 5 acres of farm land.

107
00:10:09,738 --> 00:10:10,912
5 acres, eh.

108
00:10:11,002 --> 00:10:13,055
I have a jade medal in possession.

109
00:10:16,129 --> 00:10:18,136
How much is this broken thingy worth?

110
00:10:18,329 --> 00:10:19,911
A lot.

111
00:10:21,030 --> 00:10:23,129
I'll keep it as a gift.

112
00:10:23,830 --> 00:10:25,695
But I don't believe you.

113
00:10:29,759 --> 00:10:32,611
Wei's soldier:
He's one of us. Still alive.

114
00:10:32,837 --> 00:10:35,616
We were ambushed...
[Groans in great pain]

115
00:10:36,017 --> 00:10:39,017
[Thundering]

116
00:10:46,534 --> 00:10:47,747
Big Soldier:
Anybody home?

117
00:10:56,085 --> 00:10:57,717
Anybody home?

118
00:11:02,694 --> 00:11:07,494
[Gasping]
[Moaning]

119
00:11:08,895 --> 00:11:12,339
Somebody, bring me meatloaf and liquor!

120
00:11:12,916 --> 00:11:13,916
Hey.

121
00:11:14,117 --> 00:11:17,041
A big shot like you,
what would you say now, huh?

122
00:11:17,101 --> 00:11:19,793
"Absurd!
Take him outside for beheading."

123
00:11:32,055 --> 00:11:34,140
<i>Big Soldier:
Nothing to eat in here.</i>

124
00:11:47,241 --> 00:11:50,541
Whoa! Hmm...

125
00:11:55,902 --> 00:11:58,002
[Yelling]

126
00:12:07,351 --> 00:12:09,450
Woman:
General, spare me.

127
00:12:10,651 --> 00:12:11,551
[Sighs]

128
00:12:11,640 --> 00:12:13,644
Wu: Liang's archer and infantry unit;
2,000 men in total.

129
00:12:13,835 --> 00:12:15,701
Ambushed our 1,000-strong elite unit.

130
00:12:15,889 --> 00:12:17,755
Both sides were totally wiped out.

131
00:12:17,945 --> 00:12:19,864
Prince Wen:
This is the sword I gave him.

132
00:12:21,123 --> 00:12:22,570
But where is he now?

133
00:12:22,853 --> 00:12:24,484
Wu:
I believe we will find him.

134
00:12:25,326 --> 00:12:26,893
Prince:
Wu,

135
00:12:29,382 --> 00:12:32,455
only if he's still among the living.

136
00:12:36,415 --> 00:12:38,340
Big Soldier:
War is everywhere now,

137
00:12:39,227 --> 00:12:41,699
where else you can go?

138
00:12:42,724 --> 00:12:44,496
Woman:
General, have you heard of Shen Shu?

139
00:12:44,686 --> 00:12:47,297
The one in Mt. Phoenix?
A fortunate-telling tree.

140
00:12:49,126 --> 00:12:50,946
Is he your captive?

141
00:12:51,599 --> 00:12:53,697
He's my good luck.

142
00:12:54,491 --> 00:12:56,960
Hang in there.
We're almost there.

143
00:12:57,152 --> 00:12:58,876
Wei's General:
How far?

144
00:12:59,067 --> 00:13:00,501
2 days.
[Groans]

145
00:13:05,973 --> 00:13:06,907
Small potato.

146
00:13:07,050 --> 00:13:08,263
Don't make me do this.

147
00:13:10,034 --> 00:13:11,155
Don't.

148
00:13:14,567 --> 00:13:16,553
Don't push your luck.

149
00:13:18,857 --> 00:13:20,334
Wei's General:
Give me liquor.

150
00:13:20,711 --> 00:13:22,958
- No can do.
- Liquor.

151
00:13:31,477 --> 00:13:33,157
Woman:
You've fought many battles, haven't you?

152
00:13:33,347 --> 00:13:37,002
Big Soldier: Many.
You can say I'm a big time warrior.

153
00:13:37,136 --> 00:13:39,215
[Wei's General whispering]
Untie me.

154
00:13:40,540 --> 00:13:42,265
Woman:
Then you must have killed a lot.

155
00:13:42,409 --> 00:13:43,529
Big Soldier:
Just too many.

156
00:13:43,719 --> 00:13:46,815
Fought against 8 men at a time.
Like yesterday.

157
00:13:47,016 --> 00:13:49,516
[Door falls]

158
00:13:51,017 --> 00:13:52,717
[Raining]

159
00:13:53,223 --> 00:13:55,134
Woman:
General, would you take me too?

160
00:13:55,326 --> 00:13:57,050
I'd like to become your captive.

161
00:14:00,708 --> 00:14:02,040
Okay.

162
00:14:02,508 --> 00:14:04,932
I know some musical.

163
00:14:05,121 --> 00:14:08,337
General, keep drinking.
I'll entertain you.

164
00:14:11,402 --> 00:14:13,508
[Woman singing]

165
00:14:13,843 --> 00:14:19,108
Man: If he turns out to be alive, what then?
Wu: Keep in mind that he's already dead.

166
00:14:20,009 --> 00:14:23,009
[Woman continues singing]

167
00:14:48,804 --> 00:14:50,204
[Groaning]

168
00:15:07,005 --> 00:15:08,205
[Slapping]

169
00:15:09,455 --> 00:15:11,255
[Big Soldier whispering]
Why?

170
00:15:12,765 --> 00:15:16,261
[Woman speaking softly]
General, you've killed so many.

171
00:15:16,683 --> 00:15:18,874
[Mumbling]
I'm not a General.

172
00:15:21,763 --> 00:15:24,766
My family were killed by yours.

173
00:15:25,326 --> 00:15:27,377
And I live to sing against my will.

174
00:15:27,521 --> 00:15:29,023
I'm supposed to give you a good time

175
00:15:29,166 --> 00:15:31,172
and serve you, General.

176
00:15:34,064 --> 00:15:36,869
I didn't take pleasure in
drinking with you.

177
00:15:36,970 --> 00:15:37,970
[Groaning]

178
00:16:17,201 --> 00:16:18,971
[Groaning]

179
00:16:30,351 --> 00:16:32,303
Hey, no more fight.

180
00:16:54,804 --> 00:16:56,004
Big Soldier:
Huh?

181
00:17:03,277 --> 00:17:06,277
[Instrumental music playing]

182
00:17:10,078 --> 00:17:14,120
Big Soldier:
Hey! Open the gate. I'm a soldier.

183
00:17:14,267 --> 00:17:16,548
I have taken a Wei's General...
[Gate opens]

184
00:17:16,749 --> 00:17:18,249
[Music stops]

185
00:17:26,100 --> 00:17:29,100
[Instrumental music playing]

186
00:17:32,103 --> 00:17:33,828
Man in wagon:
Stop.

187
00:17:38,135 --> 00:17:39,534
Guard:
Whose this head?

188
00:17:39,699 --> 00:17:41,745
Big Soldier:
A General of Wei.

189
00:17:43,618 --> 00:17:46,618
[Crowd whispering]

190
00:17:47,619 --> 00:17:49,859
That's him. I'm sure.

191
00:17:50,002 --> 00:17:52,519
That's a head of Wei's General.

192
00:17:52,620 --> 00:17:55,120
[Clears throat]
Reward him.

193
00:17:55,321 --> 00:17:56,860
Man:
Just a sec.

194
00:17:57,421 --> 00:17:58,741
Who killed him?

195
00:17:58,884 --> 00:17:59,911
I did.

196
00:18:00,006 --> 00:18:01,642
You? Really, huh?

197
00:18:02,899 --> 00:18:05,990
He must be an AWOL.
Cut off a dead man's head.

198
00:18:07,512 --> 00:18:08,930
Man in wagon:
Behead him.

199
00:18:12,320 --> 00:18:14,144
That's not true!

200
00:18:21,005 --> 00:18:23,145
[Yelling]
[Sword slashing]

201
00:18:24,446 --> 00:18:27,446
[Water dripping]

202
00:18:44,005 --> 00:18:45,505
Where's the horse?

203
00:18:45,906 --> 00:18:48,906
[Breathing heavily]

204
00:19:02,596 --> 00:19:04,196
[Yelling]

205
00:19:05,497 --> 00:19:07,702
Wei's General: You gonna have to
kill me if you don't let me go.

206
00:19:07,847 --> 00:19:09,664
Or I'll kill you in a heart beat.

207
00:19:10,598 --> 00:19:12,091
Big Soldier:
Kill, kill, kill.

208
00:19:12,292 --> 00:19:13,599
I grow farms.

209
00:19:13,788 --> 00:19:16,444
I don't kill and I don't want to kill.

210
00:19:16,588 --> 00:19:18,360
Big Brother:
You're getting me mad.

211
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:20,507
I'm not gonna kill you.

212
00:19:20,650 --> 00:19:22,796
Big Soldier: Can't believe
I just got fooled by some woman.

213
00:19:23,962 --> 00:19:27,008
I gave her food to eat,
and she gave me pill to swallow.

214
00:19:27,655 --> 00:19:31,245
Wei's General: You deceived her first,
so it sounds fair.

215
00:19:31,851 --> 00:19:34,088
Big Soldier:
She should have hit you instead.

216
00:19:34,371 --> 00:19:36,003
Stupid helmet.

217
00:19:38,985 --> 00:19:41,362
What did she say to you last night?

218
00:19:42,573 --> 00:19:45,885
[Chuckling]
You small potato.

219
00:19:47,886 --> 00:19:50,886
[Instrumental music playing]

220
00:19:52,400 --> 00:19:54,615
Prince:
Who's stronger, me or him?

221
00:19:54,709 --> 00:19:55,750
Wu:
He's a natural.

222
00:19:55,891 --> 00:19:58,328
Prince: So I'm nowhere to compete with him?
Wu: You're too soft and he got the heart.

223
00:19:58,467 --> 00:20:00,270
To become the King,

224
00:20:02,867 --> 00:20:04,830
you must learn from him.

225
00:20:05,085 --> 00:20:07,714
Wu: I'll take a unit and head for Liang's.
Why don't you go back...

226
00:20:07,803 --> 00:20:10,227
Prince:
I won't go back until I see him.

227
00:20:10,881 --> 00:20:12,095
Big Soldier:
You know what,

228
00:20:12,224 --> 00:20:14,336
I've been looking forward to

229
00:20:14,572 --> 00:20:18,112
life of peace and farms to grow
for 20 years.

230
00:20:26,203 --> 00:20:29,203
[Instrumental music playing]

231
00:20:46,373 --> 00:20:47,373
[Music stops]

232
00:20:47,574 --> 00:20:51,097
Soldier: The wagon is not here.
The rope was cut off.

233
00:20:57,500 --> 00:20:59,008
[Sighs]

234
00:21:00,809 --> 00:21:01,909
Hey.

235
00:21:05,210 --> 00:21:07,510
Hey. Hey?

236
00:21:07,711 --> 00:21:10,711
[Instrumental music playing]

237
00:21:18,367 --> 00:21:20,367
[Spitting]

238
00:21:20,568 --> 00:21:24,147
Big Soldier: Stop playing dead.
I'm too smart for that.

239
00:21:27,007 --> 00:21:28,507
[Music stops]

240
00:21:29,508 --> 00:21:31,548
[Horse running]

241
00:21:50,764 --> 00:21:52,500
We better stay away from the main road.

242
00:21:52,690 --> 00:21:54,183
Let's take a detour.

243
00:21:54,318 --> 00:21:58,312
Like this track.
Just don't lose the map.

244
00:22:02,345 --> 00:22:04,650
Strong liquor. Must be Liang's.

245
00:22:06,806 --> 00:22:12,319
<i>[Big Soldier singing] One small track
leads the way to home.</i>

246
00:22:20,350 --> 00:22:22,046
Wei's General:
What now?

247
00:22:24,153 --> 00:22:28,533
Like my dad said, step in shit.
Something good awaits me.

248
00:22:29,002 --> 00:22:30,355
Wei's General:
It's an ambush.

249
00:22:30,544 --> 00:22:32,601
Big Soldier:
Yeah, right.

250
00:22:37,766 --> 00:22:40,795
Bum leader:
What's loaded on that wagon?

251
00:22:40,986 --> 00:22:43,226
- Nothing particular.
- Rip him.

252
00:22:44,313 --> 00:22:46,319
Rip him off!
[Instrumental music playing]

253
00:22:49,709 --> 00:22:52,038
Big Soldier: Wait, wait...
Bum leader: Who are you?

254
00:22:52,276 --> 00:22:53,815
[Music pauses]
A General.

255
00:22:55,911 --> 00:22:58,056
Says you.

256
00:22:59,549 --> 00:23:01,573
Beat him.
Wei's General: Hmm?

257
00:23:01,787 --> 00:23:03,654
Beat him down.
[Instrumental music playing]

258
00:23:03,797 --> 00:23:05,754
Stop!

259
00:23:09,786 --> 00:23:11,208
Stop! Stop!

260
00:23:12,746 --> 00:23:13,728
Sorry.

261
00:23:17,457 --> 00:23:18,810
Please... stop.
[Music stops]

262
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:21,648
Take whatever you want,
just let us go.

263
00:23:22,585 --> 00:23:24,719
What possibly do you have,
besides this piece of junk?

264
00:23:24,839 --> 00:23:25,719
Bum:
I want revenge!

265
00:23:25,862 --> 00:23:27,541
Shut your mouth!

266
00:23:28,288 --> 00:23:30,525
Bum leader:
Who's this guy?

267
00:23:31,134 --> 00:23:32,541
He?

268
00:23:32,776 --> 00:23:34,316
He... he's my son.

269
00:23:34,506 --> 00:23:35,643
No! I'm not his son...

270
00:23:35,833 --> 00:23:37,221
You little prick!

271
00:23:39,807 --> 00:23:42,436
He's crazy. He thinks he's going to war.
I'm taking him back to grow farms.

272
00:23:42,549 --> 00:23:44,462
Grow farms? There's nothing left
to grow because of the wars.

273
00:23:44,651 --> 00:23:46,452
- Revenge!
- Get lost!

274
00:23:46,597 --> 00:23:49,467
I'm in charge here.
I say we take the wagon.

275
00:23:49,666 --> 00:23:51,466
Woman bum:
Unfaithful prick!

276
00:23:54,002 --> 00:23:56,792
Bum leader: You got a death wish?
This helmet will get you killed.

277
00:23:56,882 --> 00:23:59,876
Bum: How about this?
Bum leader: This? Will you ever learn?

278
00:23:59,935 --> 00:24:01,938
Let's go!

279
00:24:05,139 --> 00:24:06,639
[Shield drops]

280
00:24:11,740 --> 00:24:13,000
Bang!

281
00:24:17,541 --> 00:24:19,127
Bunch of fools.

282
00:24:19,985 --> 00:24:22,743
They had no idea you're the MVP
"Most Valuable Package", huh.

283
00:24:25,046 --> 00:24:26,818
[Instrumental music playing]
Your son?

284
00:24:27,009 --> 00:24:28,453
I'm gonna treat you good!

285
00:24:28,645 --> 00:24:33,907
So tie me up and
take me back to your farms!

286
00:24:33,908 --> 00:24:35,908
[Music pauses]
[Groaning]

287
00:24:38,409 --> 00:24:40,909
Hmm?
[Instrumental music playing]

288
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:47,010
[Roaring]

289
00:24:47,895 --> 00:24:50,945
[Whispering]
Don't move. Don't breathe.

290
00:24:50,946 --> 00:24:51,946
[Music pauses]

291
00:24:51,947 --> 00:24:53,947
[Licking]

292
00:24:59,046 --> 00:25:03,606
[Licking]
[Sniffing]

293
00:25:07,407 --> 00:25:11,007
[Licking]
[Swallowing]

294
00:25:17,108 --> 00:25:19,008
[Exhaling heavily]

295
00:25:20,809 --> 00:25:22,509
[Bird trilling]

296
00:25:22,910 --> 00:25:25,910
Ah!
[Groaning]

297
00:25:26,440 --> 00:25:28,176
You were trying to
strangle me to death?

298
00:25:30,145 --> 00:25:32,695
If it wasn't me...
[Groaning]

299
00:25:36,509 --> 00:25:40,509
[Groaning in pain]
[Instrumental music playing]

300
00:25:42,810 --> 00:25:44,811
[Groaning in pain]

301
00:25:45,210 --> 00:25:47,721
Prick!

302
00:25:48,022 --> 00:25:50,722
[Gasping]

303
00:26:02,195 --> 00:26:04,000
It's not Dim Mak.

304
00:26:04,328 --> 00:26:07,898
My dad was right.
I stepped in shit.

305
00:26:10,490 --> 00:26:11,748
Pretty good.

306
00:26:16,673 --> 00:26:18,505
Don't hurt us. I'm begging you!

307
00:26:29,818 --> 00:26:31,819
Prince:
Hold it there.

308
00:26:39,322 --> 00:26:42,957
I could kill him,
or I could spare him.

309
00:26:43,239 --> 00:26:45,010
I just have the power.

310
00:26:48,458 --> 00:26:52,138
Big Soldier: 1 acre for growing beans.
1 acre for melons.

311
00:26:52,886 --> 00:26:56,800
How about 2 acres for beans,
2 acres for white grains?

312
00:26:57,207 --> 00:27:00,017
No! 3 acres for beans.

313
00:27:00,818 --> 00:27:03,818
[Gasping]

314
00:27:10,282 --> 00:27:11,790
Tell me,

315
00:27:12,402 --> 00:27:15,480
what I should do with
5 acres of farmland?

316
00:27:15,670 --> 00:27:17,035
Wei's General:
I can offer you a thousand acres.

317
00:27:17,225 --> 00:27:18,538
That's too much.

318
00:27:18,729 --> 00:27:21,526
I couldn't handle that much.

319
00:27:23,343 --> 00:27:27,072
White grain or bean,
what to grow, huh?

320
00:27:27,261 --> 00:27:30,617
Wei's General:
I'd say rice. I love rice.

321
00:27:31,364 --> 00:27:35,001
White grain and rice are
the same thing, fool!

322
00:27:36,399 --> 00:27:37,948
You tired?

323
00:27:38,274 --> 00:27:40,593
Feeling comfy, right?
Wei's General: Hmm-mmm.

324
00:27:41,404 --> 00:27:47,594
[Yelling]

325
00:27:48,495 --> 00:27:50,095
[Groaning]

326
00:27:51,816 --> 00:27:53,309
Now I'm relieved.

327
00:27:53,778 --> 00:27:57,293
5 acres, I'd be working
my butt off.

328
00:27:57,426 --> 00:27:59,663
Right, I'll need some buffalo.

329
00:27:59,991 --> 00:28:03,149
One male, one female.

330
00:28:03,386 --> 00:28:06,320
The male will work in the farms.
The female will give milk.

331
00:28:06,410 --> 00:28:08,816
I'm dying to know how you're gonna
drag me all the way to Liang's.

332
00:28:08,959 --> 00:28:10,152
Wait, I can't milk a cow.

333
00:28:11,601 --> 00:28:14,312
So I'll need a wife who can do that.

334
00:28:17,518 --> 00:28:19,476
My eldest brother was a great warrior.

335
00:28:19,990 --> 00:28:21,344
He fought till death.

336
00:28:22,511 --> 00:28:25,427
My second brother was a honest person.

337
00:28:25,672 --> 00:28:27,685
He died on the battlefield as well.

338
00:28:29,215 --> 00:28:33,109
I'm the last seed of the family.

339
00:28:33,690 --> 00:28:36,720
General, do you have any siblings?

340
00:28:38,025 --> 00:28:40,111
- Wish I hadn't.
- Hmm?

341
00:28:41,312 --> 00:28:45,012
[Instrumental music playing]

342
00:28:52,309 --> 00:28:53,909
Why are you taking me here?

343
00:28:55,495 --> 00:28:57,108
I couldn't find 'em.

344
00:28:57,296 --> 00:29:00,431
The Mt. Phoenix is huge!
There's a lot of grounds to cover...

345
00:29:00,526 --> 00:29:01,927
Was he being tied up?

346
00:29:02,118 --> 00:29:05,892
Yes, his dad tied him up.
Said he's crazy or something...

347
00:29:06,080 --> 00:29:09,622
They both appeared to be crazy...

348
00:29:10,555 --> 00:29:11,815
Can I go back now?

349
00:29:11,916 --> 00:29:13,416
[Bow shot]

350
00:29:26,362 --> 00:29:28,262
[Moaning]

351
00:29:28,463 --> 00:29:31,463
[No dialogues]

352
00:29:31,663 --> 00:29:33,996
Revenge...

353
00:29:44,196 --> 00:29:48,901
They want to take you back from me?
It's not gonna be easy.

354
00:29:49,975 --> 00:29:51,653
I've been in battles for years,

355
00:29:52,308 --> 00:29:55,663
never seen an
elegant arrow like this one.

356
00:29:56,643 --> 00:29:59,905
I've seen this.
It's someone not friendly.

357
00:30:01,956 --> 00:30:05,525
People like you just asking this
for yourself.

358
00:30:05,965 --> 00:30:09,600
You know, they have you
and you'll die.

359
00:30:10,161 --> 00:30:12,584
I have you and you'll live.

360
00:30:12,821 --> 00:30:14,453
You are right.

361
00:30:14,782 --> 00:30:17,306
I don't want to die in vain.

362
00:30:18,325 --> 00:30:19,444
I'll come with you.

363
00:30:23,653 --> 00:30:25,342
Turns out General is afraid of death.

364
00:30:25,718 --> 00:30:27,396
If I die, I'll die with dignity.

365
00:30:39,177 --> 00:30:41,213
This way, or that way?

366
00:30:41,288 --> 00:30:44,605
Wei's General: Even if we make it to Liang's,
I could make a truce

367
00:30:44,795 --> 00:30:46,381
with one condition: your execution.

368
00:30:46,570 --> 00:30:48,927
Don't fool me.
Nobody fools me.

369
00:30:49,089 --> 00:30:51,374
Except that woman who drugged you.

370
00:30:51,606 --> 00:30:53,359
You have lots of women, huh?

371
00:30:54,094 --> 00:30:58,181
Wei's General: Let's talk about you.
What type of women you like?

372
00:30:58,802 --> 00:31:00,408
We have the lustful,

373
00:31:01,572 --> 00:31:03,958
and the educated.

374
00:31:04,491 --> 00:31:06,216
Big Soldier:
I like the honest ones.

375
00:31:07,242 --> 00:31:10,690
But I'd probably take the educated.
She could teach me how to read.

376
00:31:19,306 --> 00:31:21,351
You don't have a woman, right?

377
00:31:24,057 --> 00:31:25,737
That woman, what did she say to you?

378
00:31:25,972 --> 00:31:29,346
I'll tell you, if you can make it
back to Liang's.

379
00:31:29,794 --> 00:31:31,202
Wu: You guys, go down there.

380
00:31:31,390 --> 00:31:33,535
Back to where we came.
Keep a lookout.

381
00:31:46,689 --> 00:31:48,274
Prince:
Who is that?

382
00:31:49,302 --> 00:31:52,749
The Others.
They're bound to their own rules.

383
00:31:53,636 --> 00:31:55,175
Go make your acquaintance.

384
00:31:55,364 --> 00:31:56,437
Wu:
They don't speak our language.

385
00:31:56,581 --> 00:31:58,770
They are passionate people.
Good fighters too.

386
00:31:59,145 --> 00:32:00,638
Better stay away from 'em.

387
00:32:03,503 --> 00:32:05,903
[Relaxing music playing]

388
00:32:07,004 --> 00:32:10,068
Big Soldier:
Hurry up, you don't look that tired.

389
00:32:11,503 --> 00:32:14,030
Wei's General:
Birds are gathering around,

390
00:32:14,203 --> 00:32:17,730
but Phoenixes don't go with the flow.

391
00:32:18,257 --> 00:32:21,518
What chicken and ducks
are you talking about?

392
00:32:22,172 --> 00:32:25,706
If a phoenix lost its fur,
it'd make a chicken look elegant.

393
00:32:30,095 --> 00:32:31,195
Wei's General:
Huh?

394
00:32:31,396 --> 00:32:33,428
You're good at throwing rocks.

395
00:32:34,100 --> 00:32:36,792
I used to hunt wild chicken
with rocks when I was a boy.

396
00:32:37,849 --> 00:32:38,749
Hey.

397
00:32:38,950 --> 00:32:41,373
You know why our troops camped
at the Mt. Phoenix?

398
00:32:41,516 --> 00:32:42,729
How would I know?

399
00:32:42,919 --> 00:32:46,269
Nevertheless, we had hidden there
for 2 days waiting for you.

400
00:32:47,347 --> 00:32:49,518
That's what I thought, a set up.

401
00:32:49,958 --> 00:32:51,589
If it wasn't an ambush,

402
00:32:51,779 --> 00:32:55,003
my elite unit would have
crushed you majorly

403
00:32:55,309 --> 00:32:58,003
and conquered Liang.

404
00:32:59,608 --> 00:33:03,288
Stop the nonsense.
We are not that weak.

405
00:33:04,036 --> 00:33:07,986
Anyway, an AWOL like you,
it's a shame to Liang.

406
00:33:08,287 --> 00:33:11,787
[Music stops]
[Bird trilling]

407
00:33:25,850 --> 00:33:29,046
Big Soldier:
Now, see how you elite you are.

408
00:33:32,718 --> 00:33:35,096
General versus AWOL private?

409
00:33:37,299 --> 00:33:40,116
Liang versus Wei. Fair and simple.

410
00:33:40,329 --> 00:33:43,478
You want fair?
Keep your hands off my wound.

411
00:33:45,184 --> 00:33:46,862
You have your wish.

412
00:33:47,463 --> 00:33:49,963
[Instrumental music playing]

413
00:33:56,104 --> 00:33:57,864
Wei's General:
Mmm?

414
00:34:37,514 --> 00:34:38,819
You're dead.

415
00:34:40,635 --> 00:34:43,106
Ha! You're dead too.
We're both dead.

416
00:34:43,213 --> 00:34:44,380
Pervert.

417
00:34:45,501 --> 00:34:46,781
[Groaning]

418
00:34:49,302 --> 00:34:51,582
[Spring bouncing]
Huh?

419
00:34:54,523 --> 00:34:55,523
Ouch!

420
00:34:55,624 --> 00:34:58,162
War is over. Wei won.

421
00:34:59,603 --> 00:35:00,923
Oww!

422
00:35:04,504 --> 00:35:08,024
[Horses running]

423
00:35:09,325 --> 00:35:13,025
[Horses whinnying]

424
00:35:13,926 --> 00:35:15,126
Oww!

425
00:34:55,624 --> 00:34:57,862
War is over. Wei won.

426
00:35:19,444 --> 00:35:22,678
Wars have been around these years.
More people have joined the military.

427
00:35:22,821 --> 00:35:24,221
He kills him, and he gets killed by him.

428
00:35:24,411 --> 00:35:26,464
What's the attraction?

429
00:35:27,814 --> 00:35:30,516
Liang wins. Liang wins.

430
00:35:31,682 --> 00:35:33,762
You call this fair?

431
00:35:34,116 --> 00:35:36,667
It's war.
No such thing as being fair.

432
00:35:37,268 --> 00:35:40,368
[Horses whinnying]

433
00:35:47,387 --> 00:35:51,188
We'll soon have meat to eat.
Now, have some appetizer.

434
00:35:51,489 --> 00:35:54,489
[Relaxing music playing]

435
00:35:59,031 --> 00:36:00,477
Lost your appetite?

436
00:36:02,210 --> 00:36:03,701
Fine by me.

437
00:36:10,035 --> 00:36:14,082
General, what do you eat when
there is no war to go to?

438
00:36:16,138 --> 00:36:18,980
Meat and seafood.

439
00:36:19,680 --> 00:36:22,663
Any good food you can
possibly think of.

440
00:36:23,325 --> 00:36:25,409
Now I get it.
You people constantly go to war

441
00:36:25,505 --> 00:36:27,509
just because of digestion problems.

442
00:36:30,125 --> 00:36:32,456
Didn't you say you can't read, huh?

443
00:36:35,111 --> 00:36:38,978
My dad taught me these 2 words.
They are the easiest to write.

444
00:36:42,051 --> 00:36:45,577
These 2 words are not easy
to write at all.

445
00:36:46,302 --> 00:36:47,841
Why don't you go to Wei with me.

446
00:36:48,729 --> 00:36:50,314
I can offer you a high position.

447
00:36:50,503 --> 00:36:51,669
I forgot to tell you one thing.

448
00:36:51,860 --> 00:36:55,500
General alive, the rewards will be farmland
and money. No more serving in military.

449
00:36:55,682 --> 00:36:58,300
There will be no more killing for me.
Just me and the farms.

450
00:36:58,489 --> 00:37:00,999
When there's a war, there's a winner.

451
00:37:01,419 --> 00:37:05,146
A winner of unification of China.
Only that will put an end to wars.

452
00:37:05,383 --> 00:37:08,318
Only that will give you small potato
a normal life.

453
00:37:08,507 --> 00:37:09,497
You know what,

454
00:37:09,686 --> 00:37:11,406
we could have
lived our normal life,

455
00:37:11,597 --> 00:37:13,692
if you had just left us alone!

456
00:37:17,565 --> 00:37:18,730
You really don't want a bite?

457
00:37:18,884 --> 00:37:22,154
Frankly, I'm a bit hungry.

458
00:37:53,174 --> 00:37:55,573
Here comes our meat!
[Chuckling]

459
00:37:55,601 --> 00:37:57,465
Wonderful meat.

460
00:37:59,806 --> 00:38:01,466
Hmm.

461
00:38:02,006 --> 00:38:04,631
Hey! I'll get you firewood.

462
00:38:04,813 --> 00:38:08,006
[Sighs]
You have babies. Can't eat you.

463
00:38:08,699 --> 00:38:10,153
My dad said...

464
00:38:15,228 --> 00:38:16,887
[Big Soldier whispering]
Let's go. Let's go!

465
00:38:17,048 --> 00:38:18,726
Someone is coming. Let's go!

466
00:38:18,869 --> 00:38:21,524
Wei's General:
Why the panic? He's alone.

467
00:38:25,325 --> 00:38:26,925
[Horse whinnying]

468
00:38:29,506 --> 00:38:31,026
[Horse whinnying]

469
00:38:33,807 --> 00:38:35,827
[Horse whinnying]

470
00:38:38,708 --> 00:38:40,628
[Sword scrapes]

471
00:38:43,909 --> 00:38:45,029
Big Soldier:
Huh?

472
00:38:45,550 --> 00:38:47,041
It's our guy.

473
00:38:50,907 --> 00:38:53,478
Hey, bro... Hmm?

474
00:38:53,879 --> 00:38:54,879
Huh?

475
00:38:55,180 --> 00:38:56,380
[Wei's General chuckling]

476
00:38:56,781 --> 00:38:58,081
Huh!

477
00:38:58,680 --> 00:39:00,183
Bastard!

478
00:39:16,300 --> 00:39:20,810
[Gasping]

479
00:39:22,011 --> 00:39:25,021
<i>Man:
You. Go that way.</i>

480
00:39:36,622 --> 00:39:38,122
[Gasping]

481
00:39:44,328 --> 00:39:46,859
<i>Man:
A Liang-made sword.</i>

482
00:39:54,360 --> 00:39:56,060
[Exhales heavily]

483
00:40:00,201 --> 00:40:02,961
[Chuckles]
[Arrow impacts]

484
00:40:10,595 --> 00:40:12,208
On your Knees.

485
00:40:13,028 --> 00:40:16,067
I'm a Liang's soldier.
I only knee to Liang's superiors.

486
00:40:17,168 --> 00:40:19,168
[Groaning]

487
00:40:20,344 --> 00:40:23,001
Liang's scout: Now what?
Wu: You are a scout from Liang's.

488
00:40:23,195 --> 00:40:24,005
Yes.

489
00:40:24,100 --> 00:40:25,609
Wu: What about you?
Big Soldier: I'm a scout too.

490
00:40:25,749 --> 00:40:26,636
What are you scouting for?

491
00:40:26,779 --> 00:40:28,132
I'm going to the battlefield
at Mt. Phoenix. No...

492
00:40:28,227 --> 00:40:29,813
Big Soldier:
No survivors found.

493
00:40:29,932 --> 00:40:31,237
Wu:
Why taking small track?

494
00:40:31,520 --> 00:40:32,593
Liang's scout:
Your convoy is taking the main road...

495
00:40:32,734 --> 00:40:35,809
Big Soldier:
Track is faster... pretty fast.

496
00:40:36,007 --> 00:40:38,628
Liang's scout: I don't know him.
Big Soldier: What?

497
00:40:39,008 --> 00:40:41,345
He's got lightheaded
after falling off from a horse.

498
00:40:41,524 --> 00:40:43,391
Liang's scout:
No... Yes, I fell...

499
00:40:43,581 --> 00:40:46,640
- Either way I don't know you.
Big Soldier: What?

500
00:40:46,816 --> 00:40:49,193
You don't kill scouts.
That's agreement during wars.

501
00:40:49,336 --> 00:40:51,722
Wu: Is this your sword?
Big Soldier: Yes.

502
00:40:51,907 --> 00:40:53,820
Why you're carrying
a General type sword?

503
00:40:54,057 --> 00:40:56,815
Big Soldier: I borrowed it...
Wu: You're not a scout.

504
00:40:59,415 --> 00:41:01,815
Big Soldier: No, I'm not.
Wu: Where is the Wei's General?

505
00:41:02,023 --> 00:41:03,235
I don't know.

506
00:41:03,426 --> 00:41:05,277
Wu:
Don't you lie to me!

507
00:41:05,658 --> 00:41:07,703
[Gasping]
I know, I know.

508
00:41:07,903 --> 00:41:09,815
I've got your General.

509
00:41:10,005 --> 00:41:11,564
You got balls.

510
00:41:13,780 --> 00:41:15,809
Big Soldier: I got no balls!
Wu: Where is he?

511
00:41:15,992 --> 00:41:17,809
- He's fled.
- You're no use to us then.

512
00:41:17,966 --> 00:41:19,725
No. No. I-I hid him.

