774
01:05:25,652 --> 01:05:29,005
as long as you still alive,
it's pretty good.

775
01:05:29,242 --> 01:05:30,553
Must I become the King?

776
01:05:30,644 --> 01:05:33,997
You'll be a good King.
It's a good thing for Wei.

777
01:05:34,054 --> 01:05:37,550
Are you trying to convince me
to kill him without a blink of an eye?

778
01:05:37,693 --> 01:05:41,099
Wu: We've gone this far,
this is the only way out.

779
01:05:41,282 --> 01:05:44,179
Okay, how can he die

780
01:05:45,764 --> 01:05:47,720
with dignity?

781
01:05:48,886 --> 01:05:50,286
Wei's General:
What are you thinking?

782
01:05:51,731 --> 01:05:53,082
Rapeseed flower.

783
01:05:55,787 --> 01:05:57,605
I'm thinking about growing rapeseed.

784
01:05:57,748 --> 01:05:58,821
Why?

785
01:05:59,010 --> 01:05:59,943
Why what?

786
01:06:00,134 --> 01:06:03,184
Why am I being stuck
in a place like this?

787
01:06:03,547 --> 01:06:06,948
I should be the one who brings
all the Dukes to their knees.

788
01:06:07,183 --> 01:06:09,419
And then have a huge tomb
made for me.

789
01:06:09,610 --> 01:06:13,110
Have my own treasure
buried with me.

790
01:06:13,896 --> 01:06:16,453
Now they can't even
find my corpse.

791
01:06:17,066 --> 01:06:22,095
Yeah, the rest of reward money
would go to my new pharmacy store.

792
01:06:22,286 --> 01:06:25,500
To be honest, your drugs worked.

793
01:06:25,874 --> 01:06:29,456
I'm appointing you as
The Minister for Health.

794
01:06:29,557 --> 01:06:32,057
[Chuckling]

795
01:06:34,024 --> 01:06:38,522
You know what, if it wasn't the wars,
we could have been buddies.

796
01:06:39,242 --> 01:06:40,732
Perhaps.

797
01:06:42,271 --> 01:06:44,135
If you make it out alive,

798
01:06:44,743 --> 01:06:47,910
will you promise me one thing?

799
01:06:48,100 --> 01:06:49,312
Shoot.

800
01:06:51,455 --> 01:06:54,525
Never invade my nation, Liang.

801
01:07:01,021 --> 01:07:02,421
[Sighs]

802
01:07:02,722 --> 01:07:06,339
I give you 10 years of truce.
[Chuckling]

803
01:07:06,730 --> 01:07:10,251
Sounds tricky.
You have an agreement.

804
01:07:13,911 --> 01:07:15,775
And you need to promise me one thing.

805
01:07:15,876 --> 01:07:16,776
Shoot.

806
01:07:16,855 --> 01:07:18,672
If you ever make it out alive,

807
01:07:19,512 --> 01:07:21,376
you must tell them that

808
01:07:23,613 --> 01:07:24,964
I died fighting.

809
01:07:25,619 --> 01:07:28,459
I died fighting for my people.

810
01:07:29,346 --> 01:07:31,594
I've done nothing disgraceful
to Wei.

811
01:07:33,029 --> 01:07:38,523
We all bite the dust,
but not our flag.

812
01:07:40,899 --> 01:07:42,679
Don't lie to me,

813
01:07:43,519 --> 01:07:45,478
you small potato.

814
01:07:46,457 --> 01:07:48,500
Being a small potato...

815
01:07:48,957 --> 01:07:51,490
sounds pretty good.

816
01:07:54,601 --> 01:07:56,001
[Sighs]

817
01:08:07,002 --> 01:08:11,002
[Crowd cheering in distance]

818
01:08:11,803 --> 01:08:15,803
[Crowd chuckling in distance]

819
01:08:29,804 --> 01:08:31,304
[Sighs]

820
01:08:39,505 --> 01:08:41,005
Ha!

821
01:08:59,806 --> 01:09:01,006
[Pulling bow string]

822
01:09:03,807 --> 01:09:07,007
[Gasping]

823
01:09:07,508 --> 01:09:12,008
[Sparrow trilling]

824
01:09:16,109 --> 01:09:18,009
[Exhales heavily]

825
01:09:29,106 --> 01:09:30,906
Hey! Hey!

826
01:09:31,307 --> 01:09:32,807
Ow!

827
01:09:33,137 --> 01:09:34,657
Wake up.

828
01:09:35,358 --> 01:09:36,858
[Splashing]

829
01:09:37,859 --> 01:09:41,859
[Breathing heavily]
[Cheerful music playing]

830
01:09:42,708 --> 01:09:46,008
[Gasping]

831
01:09:47,009 --> 01:09:51,009
[Gasping]

832
01:09:53,389 --> 01:09:57,301
Big Solider:
Dad, I'm alive!

833
01:09:58,422 --> 01:10:00,332
Thanks Heaven!

834
01:10:00,754 --> 01:10:03,037
Thanks Heaven!

835
01:10:04,446 --> 01:10:07,240
You know what, this is
Three Legs Cave.

836
01:10:07,383 --> 01:10:09,725
There is a fisherman's village nearby.
I'll go get a boat.

837
01:10:10,008 --> 01:10:11,312
It'll take half a day to get there.

838
01:10:11,503 --> 01:10:12,901
To where?

839
01:10:13,091 --> 01:10:15,766
To Liang, where else could it be?

840
01:10:16,494 --> 01:10:21,399
<i>Don't think about running away.
You can't survive an hour without me.</i>

841
01:10:28,647 --> 01:10:29,999
Big Soldier:
Quick, quick!

842
01:10:30,885 --> 01:10:31,912
Go hide!

843
01:10:32,103 --> 01:10:33,222
Hide from what?

844
01:10:33,411 --> 01:10:36,856
Just hide.
[Horse whinnying]

845
01:10:37,139 --> 01:10:38,691
Hold me up.

846
01:10:46,128 --> 01:10:47,386
Wei's General:
Little brother.

847
01:10:48,320 --> 01:10:50,091
Big Soldier:
Little brother?

848
01:10:51,443 --> 01:10:53,028
He's your brother?

849
01:10:53,172 --> 01:10:55,594
You've been chasing me for days.
Don't you get tired?

850
01:10:55,797 --> 01:10:56,683
Prince.

851
01:10:56,873 --> 01:10:58,039
Big Soldier:
Prince?

852
01:10:58,227 --> 01:10:59,674
Why the mourning bandana?

853
01:10:59,910 --> 01:11:01,401
It's for our father.

854
01:11:01,591 --> 01:11:04,479
Wei's General: He was very sick
when I left for battles. It's you.

855
01:11:04,631 --> 01:11:07,984
It's fate. You just cared about
waging wars to please the old man.

856
01:11:08,174 --> 01:11:11,123
If I hadn't upset him by making
peace arrangement with Liang,

857
01:11:11,292 --> 01:11:12,704
I would have been the Prince.

858
01:11:12,848 --> 01:11:15,363
You set the ambush to make sure
I'd get killed.

859
01:11:16,016 --> 01:11:17,567
Something going on between you two

860
01:11:17,757 --> 01:11:19,575
and we Liang paid with 2,000 lives.

861
01:11:19,764 --> 01:11:20,977
You're not authorized to talk to me.

862
01:11:21,166 --> 01:11:23,031
You're not authorized to talk to me.

863
01:11:24,302 --> 01:11:26,632
- Leave him out of this.
- But he's the enemy.

864
01:11:26,733 --> 01:11:28,603
He wants me to live,
but you wants me to die.

865
01:11:28,704 --> 01:11:33,514
Come on. Use that crossbow I gave you
and claim the throne of Wei.

866
01:11:36,704 --> 01:11:38,704
[Sighs]

867
01:11:40,105 --> 01:11:42,015
Wu:
You're still too soft-hearted.

868
01:11:45,016 --> 01:11:46,516
Your sword.

869
01:11:46,617 --> 01:11:50,117
Wu:
If you don't kill him, he will kill you.

870
01:11:51,018 --> 01:11:53,018
Only one of you will become the King.

871
01:11:55,819 --> 01:11:59,609
Um, that's doesn't make any sense,
why one of you brothers must die?

872
01:11:59,711 --> 01:12:02,911
- It's none of your business.
- You guys are complicating things.

873
01:12:02,912 --> 01:12:07,812
- I said "it's none of your business!"
- It's all because of that nosy baldhead.

874
01:12:09,514 --> 01:12:11,014
I'm done talking.

875
01:12:11,415 --> 01:12:14,515
[Horses whinnying]
[Instrumental music playing]

876
01:12:14,806 --> 01:12:18,806
[Horses whinnying]
[Speaking foreign language]

877
01:12:23,115 --> 01:12:25,615
He really looks upset.
Maybe we should go now.

878
01:12:31,816 --> 01:12:33,316
I'm really messed up big time.

879
01:12:33,517 --> 01:12:36,317
You do what you got to do, Master.

880
01:12:44,518 --> 01:12:46,608
[Arrow cracks]
Aah!

881
01:12:49,209 --> 01:12:51,609
[Speaking foreign language]

882
01:12:56,718 --> 01:12:59,218
Hey, can we go now, eh?

883
01:13:03,909 --> 01:13:05,419
[Sword slashes]

884
01:13:25,000 --> 01:13:28,000
[Pounding]

885
01:13:28,201 --> 01:13:29,701
[Sword scrapes]

886
01:13:43,602 --> 01:13:46,102
Aah!

887
01:13:47,003 --> 01:13:48,503
Aah!

888
01:14:08,304 --> 01:14:09,804
Huh?

889
01:14:12,805 --> 01:14:15,305
[Sighs]

890
01:14:20,696 --> 01:14:23,714
General!
Behind you!

891
01:14:27,015 --> 01:14:28,015
[Chuckling]

892
01:14:28,216 --> 01:14:29,816
It's none of my business.

893
01:14:32,717 --> 01:14:36,217
[Moaning]
What a pity.

894
01:14:36,518 --> 01:14:40,518
[Gasping]

895
01:14:55,419 --> 01:14:57,009
Whoa!

896
01:15:00,510 --> 01:15:03,610
[Groaning]

897
01:15:03,811 --> 01:15:06,811
[Weapon swinging]

898
01:15:17,012 --> 01:15:18,512
Ouch!

899
01:15:19,418 --> 01:15:21,418
Not even one small rock?

900
01:15:38,009 --> 01:15:41,009
[Gasping]

901
01:15:45,310 --> 01:15:46,810
Ow!

902
01:15:47,219 --> 01:15:48,719
Don't get any closer,

903
01:15:48,920 --> 01:15:50,920
or you'd get blind.

904
01:15:53,021 --> 01:15:54,821
<i>Big brother!</i>

905
01:16:25,322 --> 01:16:29,002
[Screaming]

906
01:16:30,503 --> 01:16:32,303
[Yelling in anger]

907
01:16:37,604 --> 01:16:39,304
[Yelling in distance]

908
01:16:44,005 --> 01:16:45,305
Whoa!

909
01:16:52,106 --> 01:16:54,306
[Gasping]

910
01:16:58,714 --> 01:17:00,714
Stop!
[Music stops]

911
01:17:01,815 --> 01:17:03,215
[Gasping]

912
01:17:03,405 --> 01:17:06,415
I'm the one you should kill.

913
01:17:06,916 --> 01:17:09,616
I'm the one you should kill.

914
01:17:10,117 --> 01:17:14,917
Me and my brother,
only one will walk out here alive.

915
01:17:16,606 --> 01:17:20,649
You don't understand
what I'm saying, do you? huh?

916
01:17:23,810 --> 01:17:26,107
How about this, huh? Ah!

917
01:17:26,389 --> 01:17:28,234
This is what I got to do.

918
01:17:28,394 --> 01:17:29,632
<i>Little brother!</i>

919
01:17:36,080 --> 01:17:37,287
Big brother,

920
01:17:38,080 --> 01:17:40,597
am I dying with dignity?

921
01:17:42,527 --> 01:17:46,967
Sorry about our big boat.

922
01:17:47,107 --> 01:17:50,568
We can never build it together.

923
01:17:51,969 --> 01:17:55,009
[Breathing heavily]

924
01:18:36,608 --> 01:18:37,866
Do me a favor.

925
01:18:39,306 --> 01:18:41,044
Help me bury him.

926
01:18:46,492 --> 01:18:50,870
We must carry on, General.
We got half day.

927
01:18:51,758 --> 01:18:54,924
Sorry, I mean Prince.

928
01:19:00,279 --> 01:19:03,315
Your Wei's liquor is not strong enough.

929
01:19:04,706 --> 01:19:06,802
I know what you're thinking.

930
01:19:06,991 --> 01:19:10,030
I also know what you're thinking.

931
01:19:12,024 --> 01:19:15,657
- Pretty good.
- We're still alive.

932
01:19:17,799 --> 01:19:22,115
You two reminded me
of my own brothers.

933
01:19:22,379 --> 01:19:23,778
Wei's Prince:
They were good soldiers.

934
01:19:23,968 --> 01:19:26,112
Big Soldier: In fact,
I wanted to be a good soldier.

935
01:19:27,510 --> 01:19:31,329
The first time we enlisted,
we 3 brothers got no choice.

936
01:19:31,565 --> 01:19:33,662
The first tour lasted for 3 years.

937
01:19:34,001 --> 01:19:35,493
When we came back,

938
01:19:36,427 --> 01:19:38,431
our village had been burnt to ground.

939
01:19:39,270 --> 01:19:41,322
We became homeless.

940
01:19:41,882 --> 01:19:44,803
Before my dad died, he told us
[Slow music playing]

941
01:19:45,016 --> 01:19:48,046
we had served our country.

942
01:19:49,008 --> 01:19:53,432
But when the wars will end?

943
01:19:54,691 --> 01:19:59,207
And he said, "kids, listen,

944
01:20:02,143 --> 01:20:04,473
one of you 3 brothers must live,

945
01:20:08,836 --> 01:20:11,633
in order to raise kids for our family."

946
01:20:12,923 --> 01:20:16,071
[Sobbing]
Now I'm the only one left.

947
01:20:20,168 --> 01:20:25,071
Having you is my biggest luck ever.

948
01:20:27,072 --> 01:20:31,072
[Sobbing continues]

949
01:20:32,786 --> 01:20:37,395
I can't say the same thing about my luck.

950
01:20:38,096 --> 01:20:42,096
[Woman singing in distance]

951
01:20:45,007 --> 01:20:49,097
[Singing continues]

952
01:20:52,709 --> 01:20:54,061
Wei's Prince:
Don't ask.

953
01:20:54,668 --> 01:20:56,906
What she said to me the other night:

954
01:20:58,536 --> 01:21:00,359
"kama".

955
01:21:00,560 --> 01:21:02,360
[Sighs]

956
01:21:02,523 --> 01:21:04,568
What a little potato.

957
01:21:06,609 --> 01:21:10,009
[Singing continues]

958
01:21:13,901 --> 01:21:16,901
Shen Shu, Mt. Phoenix.

959
01:21:21,702 --> 01:21:27,403
"Peace"

960
01:21:41,771 --> 01:21:43,316
"Mt. Liang"

961
01:21:43,459 --> 01:21:46,886
You know what,
after this turn is Liang's soil.

962
01:21:51,655 --> 01:21:55,194
My brother wanted to befriend
Liang, maybe he's right.

963
01:21:55,348 --> 01:21:58,740
If Liang's Duke spare my life, may be we could
work something out for allying each other.

964
01:21:58,860 --> 01:22:00,352
Maybe, maybe.

965
01:22:02,318 --> 01:22:03,904
Maybe it's too late.

966
01:22:04,791 --> 01:22:06,281
Maybe.

967
01:22:17,282 --> 01:22:20,702
[Breathing heavily]

968
01:22:20,945 --> 01:22:23,503
Nothing feels like home!

969
01:22:27,420 --> 01:22:29,470
That's your secret belt...

970
01:22:37,942 --> 01:22:39,674
I was wrong about you.

971
01:22:40,609 --> 01:22:43,663
Never thought you could make
this journey for both of us.

972
01:22:44,429 --> 01:22:47,793
Now, am I your captive or enemy?

973
01:22:50,904 --> 01:22:52,504
[Sword scrapes]

974
01:22:54,775 --> 01:22:57,059
Neither. Just go.

975
01:22:59,527 --> 01:23:02,560
Hurry. Before I change my mind.

976
01:23:06,382 --> 01:23:07,689
Why?

977
01:23:08,948 --> 01:23:10,605
You 2 brothers...

978
01:23:10,808 --> 01:23:12,715
one must live.

979
01:23:12,916 --> 01:23:15,016
[Grunting]

980
01:23:23,068 --> 01:23:24,605
Can I count on your word?

981
01:23:25,129 --> 01:23:26,387
What you mean?

982
01:23:26,578 --> 01:23:28,301
10 years of truce!

983
01:23:28,493 --> 01:23:31,752
Absolutely!
You have my word!

984
01:23:35,906 --> 01:23:37,445
Don't forget...

985
01:23:37,913 --> 01:23:41,099
that medal you took from me,
it's worth a fortunate.

986
01:23:41,408 --> 01:23:44,714
It can get your farmland and money.

987
01:23:46,253 --> 01:23:47,837
I found it.

988
01:23:48,438 --> 01:23:50,338
[Sighs]

989
01:23:50,586 --> 01:23:53,156
I might not live long enough...

990
01:23:54,507 --> 01:23:58,021
Now I'm empty-handed.
Pretty good.

991
01:24:01,305 --> 01:24:03,328
<i>Boy:
Run.</i>

992
01:24:04,685 --> 01:24:06,777
Run away now.

993
01:24:23,508 --> 01:24:25,778
[Soldiers cheering]

994
01:24:35,509 --> 01:24:40,009
[Cheering continues]

995
01:24:43,000 --> 01:24:45,010
[Horse whinnying]

996
01:24:45,787 --> 01:24:47,325
Officer:
Ask him to surrender.

997
01:24:49,514 --> 01:24:53,064
Liang has been destroyed.
Knee down and surrender.

998
01:24:54,872 --> 01:24:56,456
Liang is gone?

999
01:24:57,623 --> 01:24:58,882
How could that possible?

1000
01:24:59,071 --> 01:25:02,159
Officer: Liang refused to surrender.
So we, from Qin, destroyed it.

1001
01:25:02,288 --> 01:25:05,827
- Your units have been completely eliminated.
Qin's soldier: On your knee. Last chance.

1002
01:25:05,970 --> 01:25:07,835
Big Soldier:
All units wiped out?

1003
01:25:08,003 --> 01:25:09,559
No more Liang.

1004
01:25:09,960 --> 01:25:11,160
"Qin"

1005
01:25:11,296 --> 01:25:14,571
This is not happening.
[Pulling bow string]

1006
01:25:18,402 --> 01:25:23,002
[No dialogues]

1007
01:25:23,703 --> 01:25:26,003
[Bow shot]

1008
01:25:27,804 --> 01:25:31,804
[Grunts]
[Qin's soldiers chuckling]

1009
01:25:33,001 --> 01:25:35,053
Liang is history.

1010
01:25:36,961 --> 01:25:40,010
I really got nothing left now.

1011
01:25:40,887 --> 01:25:43,849
Qin's officer:
Put the flag down.

1012
01:25:50,187 --> 01:25:53,122
<i>[Prince singing]
One main road</i>

1013
01:25:53,228 --> 01:25:55,178
Qin's officer:
Your units have been wiped out.

1014
01:25:55,273 --> 01:25:57,794
Big Soldier:
That's not entirely true.

1015
01:25:57,906 --> 01:25:59,106
Qin's officer:
Drop your sword.

1016
01:25:59,307 --> 01:26:01,264
I'm still standing!
Give your best shot!

1017
01:26:01,359 --> 01:26:04,902
<i>[Singing]
My home is right at</i>

1018
01:26:07,009 --> 01:26:10,022
<i>the foot of Mt. Liang</i>

1019
01:26:10,725 --> 01:26:18,499
<i>Soils are rich there
5 acres of farms</i>

1020
01:26:19,991 --> 01:26:22,426
<i>5 acres of farm</i>

1021
01:26:22,570 --> 01:26:24,008
Sorry dad,

1022
01:26:24,500 --> 01:26:28,558
guess I'm not gonna raise
any kids now.

1023
01:26:30,682 --> 01:26:34,702
<i>[Singing]
One big river</i>

1024
01:26:35,202 --> 01:26:38,612
<i>leads to my home</i>

1025
01:26:39,891 --> 01:26:44,005
<i>My wife, my kids</i>

1026
01:26:44,401 --> 01:26:47,435
<i>and my big house</i>

1027
01:26:49,344 --> 01:26:53,606
<i>Chickens and ducks are fat</i>

1028
01:26:54,204 --> 01:26:58,096
<i>Cattle is strong</i>

1029
01:26:58,881 --> 01:27:03,224
<i>Grow some bean
white grain</i>

1030
01:27:03,681 --> 01:27:07,724
<i>and rapeseed flower</i>

1031
01:27:11,805 --> 01:27:13,805
[Spring bouncing]

1032
01:27:28,506 --> 01:27:30,906
[Sparrow trilling]

1033
01:27:31,369 --> 01:27:35,910
I ain't a shame to Liang, am I?
[Sparrow trilling]

1034
01:27:37,211 --> 01:27:39,011
"Liang"

1035
01:27:40,000 --> 01:27:45,800
SDH/translation: Arigon

